# Vercel Preview Review Mode

When preparing a docs PR for visual review on Vercel preview deploys, add temporary CSS to `src/css/custom.css` to highlight changes directly in the rendered site.

Add the CSS block below **before pushing for review**, and **remove it before merging**.

## CSS to add to `src/css/custom.css`

```css
/* === REVIEW MODE — remove before merge === */

/* Sidebar: highlight parent category when it contains a changed child page */
.theme-doc-sidebar-item-category-level-1:has(a[href*="TARGET_PAGE_SLUG"]) > .menu__list-item-collapsible > .menu__link--sublist {
  color: #FFA500 !important;
  font-weight: bold !important;
}
.theme-doc-sidebar-item-category-level-1:has(a[href*="TARGET_PAGE_SLUG"]) > .menu__list-item-collapsible > .menu__link--sublist::after {
  content: " ●";
  color: #FFA500;
  font-size: 0.7em;
}

/* Sidebar: highlight changed page links */
a[href*="TARGET_PAGE_SLUG"] {
  color: #FFA500 !important;
  font-weight: bold !important;
}
a[href*="TARGET_PAGE_SLUG"]::after {
  content: " ●";
  color: #FFA500;
  font-size: 0.7em;
}

/* Inline diff: deleted text (red strikethrough) */
del.review-diff {
  color: #ff6b6b;
  text-decoration: line-through;
  background: rgba(255, 107, 107, 0.1);
  padding: 1px 3px;
  border-radius: 2px;
}

/* Inline diff: inserted text (green highlight) */
ins.review-diff {
  color: #51cf66;
  text-decoration: none;
  background: rgba(81, 207, 102, 0.1);
  padding: 1px 3px;
  border-radius: 2px;
}

/* Section-level: new section (green left border) */
.review-new-section {
  border-left: 3px solid #51cf66;
  padding-left: 12px;
  margin-left: -15px;
}

/* Section-level: removed section (red left border) */
.review-removed-section {
  border-left: 3px solid #ff6b6b;
  padding-left: 12px;
  margin-left: -15px;
  opacity: 0.7;
}

/* === END REVIEW MODE === */
```

## Markdown usage in doc files

- Inline changes: `<del class="review-diff">old text</del><ins class="review-diff">new text</ins>`
- New sections: wrap in `<div class="review-new-section">...</div>`
- Removed sections: wrap in `<div class="review-removed-section">...</div>`

Replace `TARGET_PAGE_SLUG` with the actual page slug (e.g., `how-to-create-a-margin-account`). Duplicate the sidebar CSS blocks for each changed page.
